titleStmt.title: An alphabetical list of the knights, citizens, and burgesses, elected in the year 1698. to sit in Parliament together with an alphabet of the places that have the priviledge of election, with proper numbers and letters for the easie use therof. Note: those which have this mark * before them, were not members of the last Parliament.

publicationStmt.publisher: Printed by Edward Jones in the Savoy, and sold by Jacob Tonson in Fleet-Street, and John Nutt near Stationers-Hall,

notesStmt.note: Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
